<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/940.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The groups have decided to telegraph Russia to the following effect:
                                Japan has made a proposition which is acceptable to the British,
                                French and German Governments and to all four groups, and upon
                                approval by the American Government she will be admitted, thus
                                making five groups. Definite answer to be received from Russia by
                                June 18, else loan negotiations will proceed without her.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>